<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/615001063/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Progressive evaluation - To pass the course, the student may do first practical task (1PW during 10th week, but is not mandatory) and must do second practical work (2PW during 16th week) and get, at least, a 5 over 10 points in the second one and do the practical exam (PE - 16th week), obtaining, at least, a 5 over 10 points.
Final grade, will be: Final grade = 1PW * 0.3 + 2PW *0.5 + PE*0.2 (in case 1PW was note presented at its moment, in this formula it will be a 0)
This final grade should be at least 5 over 10 to pass the course
As it may be checked, first practical task is optional but counts a 30% of the grade

Global evaluation - To pass the course, the student must get, at least, a 5 over 10 points in the second practical task and do the practical exam (PE - 16th week), obtaining, at least, a 5 over 10 points.
First practical task may NOT be redone at this moment
Final grade, will be: Final grade = 1PW * 0.3 + 2PW *0.5 + PE*0.2 (in case 1PW was note presented at its moment, in this formula it will be a 0)
This final grade should be at least 5 over 10 to pass the course
If the student does not get the minimum grade in the second practical task or the practical exam he/she will fail the course and his/her final grade will be the minimum of the grades of the different activities done and he/she will have to attend referred examination in the extraordinary exam call.

Referred (re-sit) examination - To pass the course doing the this call for exam, the student must do, optionally, first (1PW) and second practical work, mandatory, (2PW) and get, at least, 5 points out of 10 in 2PW, and do the practical exam (PE - 16th week), obtaining, at least, a 5 over 10 points.
Final grade, will be: Final grade = 1PW * 0.3 + 2PW *0.5 + PE*0.2 (in case 1PW was note presented at its moment, in this formula it will be a 0)
This final grade should be at least 5 over 10 to pass the course

If the student does not get the minimum grade in any of the evaluation activities he/she will fail the course and his/her final grade will be the minimum of the grades of the different activities done.

ATTENTION:
- If any type of fraud is detected in any of the evaluation activities, the student/s will get a zero as final grade in the current convocatory and the teacher may propose a special and equivalent exam in the next call for exam.
- The teacher may ask any student at any time to present and/or defend any of the evaluation activities throughout the course. If said presentation/defense is not carried out satisfactorily, the student will fail the subject with the grade obtained in said defense."""@es ;
    ns1:hasEvaluationTrial <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/615001063/2025-26/evaluation/trial1>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/615001063/2025-26/evaluation/trial2>,
        <https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/615001063/2025-26/evaluation/trial3>,
